Peru Stocks: Credicorp, Intergroup, Maple, Relapasa, Volcan

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-09-02T17:20:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-02/peru-stocks-credicorp-intergroup-maple-relapasa-volcan.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 12:54 p.m.  New York  time.  The Lima General Index fell 1 percent to 20,526.96. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index declined 1 percent to 2,700.60.  Industrial shares and banks dropped after U.S. stocks and
commodities declined, said Arlen Lahura, a trader at Lima-based
brokerage Coril SAB.  Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s
Repsol YPF SA known as Relapasa, fell 2.4 percent to 82 centimos
after crude fell in New York.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the
oil and natural gas producer with operations in Peru, declined
0.9 percent to $1.10. Corp. Aceros Arequipa SA (CORAREI1 PE),
the Lima-based steelmaker, slid 1.2 percent to 2.47 soles.  Intergroup Financial Services Corp. (IFS)  , the owner of
Peru’s fourth-largest bank, Interbank, dropped 1.9 percent to
$25.80.  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest financial-
services holding company, fell 1.5 percent to $99.80.  Miners declined after metals slumped in New York and
 London .  Alturas Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian gold and copper
exploration company, fell 6.7 percent to 14 cents.  Southern
Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peru’s biggest copper producer, dropped
3.5 percent to $32.20.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian
gold and copper exploration company, declined 2.1 percent to 46
cents. Volcan Cia. Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest zinc
producer, fell 2 percent to 2.95 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in  Lima  at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  